In this article, President Barack Obama proclaims May 1, 2012, as Law Day, U.S.A. He emphasizes the importance of remembering and protecting the heritage of liberty, justice, and equality under the law. The theme for this year's Law Day is "No Courts, No Justice, No Freedom," highlighting the role of courts in safeguarding the rights and liberties of Americans. Obama calls for the necessary resources and access to justice to be provided to ensure the efficient functioning of the courts. He also urges reflection on the contributions of legal and judicial professionals in building an America that upholds principles of equal protection and due process. The president encourages Americans to acknowledge the significance of the nation's legal and judicial systems through appropriate ceremonies and activities, and to display the flag of the United States in support of this observance.